Hi All,

We have now created a holistic COD management dashboard. It can be accessed
via http://admin-v2.pidge.in/
Login will only be possible via SSO using a Pidge email ID. After logging
in for the first time, please let me know so that appropriate access can be
provided. Once you have access, this will be your landing page:
[image: image.png]

Upon entering the module, the page displays global totals as well as the
account-level total below:
1. Amount Due to Pidge - This is the amount Pidge must collect from the
respective business or vendor.
2. Amount Due from Pidge - This is the amount Pidge must transfer to the
respective business or vendor.
3. Auto Remittance: Amount being remitted via the T+1 Razorpay integration

Below is a sample for reference.
[image: image.png]

For each account, options are provided to Settle "Due to Pidge" when the
amount is received in the Pidge bank account. Similarly, you can also
adjust the "Due from Pidge" amount.

*Sample of Settling Due to Pidge:*
1. Showing the business name
2. Amount pending
3. Amount Received
4. Date of record in Pidge bank account
5. UTR against which the amount was received
6. Remarks - These remarks would be visible to clients on the dashboard.
[image: image.png]



*Sample of Adjusting Due from Pidge:*
1. Business Name
2. Total Due from Pidge
3. Amount Adjusted (either transferred or settled against invoice)
4. UTR
5. Remarks describing whether the transfer to the bank was complete or
partial, with some amount cleared against the invoice. This remark will
also be visible to the client on the dashboard.
[image: image.png]


*The Dashboard is completely usable and should be considered the source of
truth for Cash Management. If a client has any questions, they can be
viewed from the COD management page on the dashboard.*

*New Request from Finance: Provide day level amount movement for each
transaction type*
We will provide the following:
1. Automated report sent via email at the end of the day
2. Total Amount added/reduced from 'Due from Pidge,' 'Due to Pidge,' and
'Auto remitted' to create tally entries


*NOTE:*
*This dashboard manages only Cash (COD) amounts. Any charges deducted for
COD handling (offline) should be deducted from wallet using the admin Panel
as it gives clear visibility of the transaction in the dashboard to client.
Remitting lesser amount with a remark to adjust cash handling fees should
not be done. A provision for adding a credit entry already exists on the
Admin Panel (v1). **Finance will manage COD handling fees manually as we
plan to roll out all businesses on the T+1 module by the end of the
quarter.*


*Please ensure that the next transfer cycle for cash transfer is managed
using the tool itself so that we ensure there is no gap and at the same
time get used to the module*

--0000000000003a3a9f06519bc0e6
